## SM-1. Business Rules — Attempts, Prompts and Retries

### SM-1.1 Plans and Attempt Quotas

The `users.plan` column enforces `('starter','pro','ultra')` via a CHECK constraint.

| Plan | Task practice? | Attempts per task | Speaking mock tests |
|------|---------------|-------------------|--------------------|
| **Starter** | Locked | 0 | 1 included |
| **Pro** | Yes | 5 per task (Tasks 0–8) | 2 included |
| **Ultra** | Yes | 15 per task (Tasks 0–8) | 5 included |

> [!NOTE]
> These numbers live in `apps/web/lib/constants.ts` (`PRO_PLAN_LIMITS.speaking_attempts_per_task`) and in `apps/api/app/core/quota.py`. The backend `quota.py` is the canonical source. Both must stay in sync.

### SM-1.2 Prompt Rotation Logic

Currently `SpeakingPromptRepository.get_active_by_task()` returns the most recently created prompt (`.order_by(created_at.desc()).limit(1)`). This must change to serve a **different, unseen prompt** on each attempt until all available prompts for a task are exhausted.

**Decision matrix:**

```
has_remaining_quota AND has_unseen_prompts  → assign next unseen prompt (oldest first)
has_remaining_quota AND no_unseen_prompts   → assign last-seen prompt (repeat)
quota_exhausted (retry allowed)             → same last-seen prompt, quota NOT deducted
```

> [!IMPORTANT]
> Retries after quota exhaustion are **free and unlimited** — they do not consume quota, do not cycle to a new prompt, and still go through the full recording + AI pipeline.

### SM-1.3 Quota Consumed vs. Bonus Retry

- **Quota is consumed** only when an attempt starts AND quota remains.
- **Retry attempts** (beyond quota) still create `attempts` rows but are flagged `is_bonus_retry = TRUE`.
- History and admin views can distinguish counted attempts from bonus retries.

